From d82896703bd9b103ee75fd3fad74949483434611 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 11:28:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman-pcd-manip: record hmct_used for RMV_ETHERNET + INSRT_GENERIC (ARCHIVED v1.3)

ARCHIVE-half of the original 0037 (v1.2 hmct_used encoders).  The
RMV_ETHERNET and INSRT_GENERIC encoders themselves are OH-port-chain
primitives that v1.3 removes from the v1.0 forward path (see plans/
ASK2-COURSE-CORRECTION.md §2 Phase 2).  These two hmct_used hunks
move here alongside their parent encoders (originally in 0033, the
RMV/INSRT half now living in this directory as
0033-fman-pcd-manip-v1.2-oh-port-primitives-RMV-INSRT-only.patch).

Kept as a bisect anchor for one release cycle.  If a future v1.1
restores OH-port for IPsec re-inject, this patch can be reapplied
alongside the matching encoder-restore patches.
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
index 06f64b7..62c9eea 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
@@ -637,6 +637,7 @@ cmd |= (u32)FMAN_PCD_L2_HDR_RMV_SIZE
 
 iowrite32be(cmd, hmct);
 
+manip->hmct_used = 4; /* PR14z: cmd word, no payload */
 *out_op = FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC;
 return hmct;
 }
@@ -701,6 +702,7 @@ iowrite32be(word, cur);
 cur += 4;
 }
 
+manip->hmct_used = 4 + (n_words * 4); /* PR14z: cmd word + payload words */
 *out_op = FMAN_PCD_HMAN_OC;
 return hmct;
 }
-- 
